🧠 Agent Brain Rules (Instructions)

📌 Why Brain Rules Are Needed

Although the selected model (Nova Pro) is powerful, without proper instructions the agent may:

Produce inconsistent responses

Take risky actions too quickly

Skip confirmation steps

Generate overly long or complex outputs

👉 To control this behavior, we define Agent Instructions (Brain Rules).

These rules ensure:

✅ Consistent tone and format

✅ Safe execution of actions

✅ Proper use of tools (Lambda)

✅ Controlled and predictable behavior



⚙️ Where to Configure

Open your agent in Amazon Bedrock

Go to Agent Builder

Scroll to Instructions for the Agent

Paste the following instructions



🧾 Agent Instructions (Brain Rules)
copy and paste instructions from instruction file



💾 Step 3: Save Configuration

Click Save & Exit



🚀 Step 4: Prepare the Agent

Go to the Test panel (right side)



Click Prepare

👉 This applies all the instructions to the agent

✅ Result of This Step

After adding Brain Rules:

✅ Agent understands when to call tools

✅ Agent follows safe deletion workflow

✅ Agent avoids risky operations

✅ Responses become structured and consistent

✅ System behaves predictably and securely



🧠 Key Insight

These instructions act as the "brain" of the system, ensuring the AI behaves like a responsible cloud engineer, not just a chatbot.
